01:06.200 --> 01:11.200
Accounting

01:11.200 --> 01:21.200
We will start with the types of accounting and their interrelationship in the organization.

01:21.200 --> 01:28.200
Accounting is a language of knowledge and rules of their use.

01:29.200 --> 01:34.200
It is created to replace real objects with their symbols.

01:36.200 --> 01:43.200
These symbols allow to describe the economic activity and its results.

01:45.200 --> 01:49.200
The language of signs is a set of conditional designations,

01:49.200 --> 01:55.200
represented primarily by professional terminology and special codes.

01:55.200 --> 02:01.200
The rules of use are the restrictions introduced into the accounting language

02:01.200 --> 02:07.200
and which establish the informational connections between the signs,

02:07.200 --> 02:15.200
providing the necessary communication between the participants of the economic process.

02:16.200 --> 02:25.200
Accounting includes the collection, accumulation and storage of information about the objects of accounting.

02:26.200 --> 02:29.200
There are different types of accounting, as we have already said.

02:29.200 --> 02:33.200
This is the management accounting system,

02:33.200 --> 02:36.200
this is the tax accounting system,

02:36.200 --> 02:39.200
this is the financial accounting system,

02:39.200 --> 02:42.200
and this is the accounting system according to the standards of the Russian Federal Reserve,

02:42.200 --> 02:45.200
according to the standards of the Federal Reserve,

02:45.200 --> 02:51.200
maybe according to the standards of the US GAAP,

02:51.200 --> 02:57.200
and each accounting system gives us its own accountability.

02:59.200 --> 03:03.200
The management accounting system will give the management accountability,

03:03.200 --> 03:07.200
the tax accounting system will give us the tax accountability,

03:07.200 --> 03:12.200
the financial accounting system will give us the financial accountability.

03:12.200 --> 03:19.200
What is the reason for such a variety of accounting?

03:19.200 --> 03:27.200
It is explained by the fact that different tasks are set before the accounting accounting system.

03:27.200 --> 03:37.200
These tasks may be the task of controlling the use of purposeful means,

03:37.200 --> 03:42.200
it may be the requirements of the state statistics,

03:42.200 --> 03:48.200
it may be the requirements that are presented by the market of securities,

03:48.200 --> 03:52.200
it may be macroeconomic regulation,

03:52.200 --> 03:56.200
it may be the resolution of civil and legal disputes,

03:56.200 --> 04:00.200
it may be the division of property during reorganization,

04:00.200 --> 04:04.200
it may be the calculation of taxes and tax administration,

04:04.200 --> 04:14.200
it may be information about the financial situation and the financial results of the organization.

04:15.200 --> 04:25.200
All this variety of accounting is caused by the fact that different users need different information.

04:25.200 --> 04:32.200
All users can be divided into internal users and external users.

04:32.200 --> 04:41.200
When we talk about internal users, we mean that this is about the owners of the enterprise,

04:41.200 --> 04:47.200
this is the members of the board of directors, this is the administration, managers,

04:47.200 --> 04:50.200
this is the line managers.

04:50.200 --> 04:54.200
They need all the information,

04:54.200 --> 05:02.200
both tax information, management information and financial accounting.

05:02.200 --> 05:09.200
External users are divided into users with indirect financial interest

05:09.200 --> 05:13.200
and with direct financial interest.

05:13.200 --> 05:18.200
With indirect financial interest, this is the local administration,

05:18.200 --> 05:23.200
which is interested in whether the enterprise will work tomorrow,

05:23.200 --> 05:31.200
how much labor it can do, what taxes it will pay.

05:31.200 --> 05:38.200
These are tax authorities that may require any information.

05:38.200 --> 05:46.200
But they are primarily interested in the correct calculation and payment of taxes to the budget.

05:46.200 --> 05:55.200
These are statistical authorities that will be interested in purely statistical information.

05:56.200 --> 06:07.200
These are buyers who will be interested in the financial accounting of the organization.

06:07.200 --> 06:13.200
Users with direct financial interest are investors,

06:13.200 --> 06:18.200
investors of today, future investors.

06:18.200 --> 06:23.200
These are creditors, these are suppliers.

06:23.200 --> 06:28.200
They are interested in financial information.

06:28.200 --> 06:39.200
The general information base for the composition of financial, management and tax accounting registers

06:39.200 --> 06:44.200
is the primary accounting document, the accounting book.

06:44.200 --> 06:49.200
In various types of financial, management and tax registers,

06:49.200 --> 06:58.200
this information is grouped according to the tasks of each type of accounting.

06:58.200 --> 07:05.200
The area of cross-referencing of financial, management and tax accounting

07:05.200 --> 07:10.200
is the determination and distribution of expenses,

07:10.200 --> 07:13.200
calculation of the cost of the finished product,

07:13.200 --> 07:18.200
the cost of the unfinished product, and so on.

07:18.200 --> 07:28.200
Financial, management and tax accounting are interconnected subsystems of a single accounting.

07:29.200 --> 07:43.200
The register of financial accounting and, accordingly, financial accounting is created on the basis of the primary accounting document.

07:43.200 --> 07:48.200
The register of management accounting and, accordingly, accounting,

07:48.200 --> 07:55.200
approved by the organization for the generalization of management accounting data,

07:55.200 --> 08:04.200
the register of tax accounting allows us to make tax declarations.

08:06.200 --> 08:12.200
Management accounting is a subsystem of accounting,

08:12.200 --> 08:18.200
which within the framework of one organization provides its apparatus with information

08:18.200 --> 08:25.200
used for planning, management and control of the organization's activities.

08:25.200 --> 08:31.200
This process includes the detection, measurement, collection, analysis, preparation,

08:31.200 --> 08:38.200
interpretation, transfer and reception of information to the necessary management apparatus

08:38.200 --> 08:41.200
for its function.

08:42.200 --> 08:49.200
The organization of management accounting is the internal affair of each enterprise.

08:49.200 --> 08:56.200
The state does not prescribe the common rules for the management accounting.

08:56.200 --> 09:05.200
Management independently determines in which sections to classify the management objects

09:05.200 --> 09:09.200
and how to carry out their accounting.

09:09.200 --> 09:18.200
Management accounting information is intended for the management and managers of the enterprise.

09:18.200 --> 09:26.200
It is a commercial secret and has a strictly confidential nature.

09:28.200 --> 09:37.200
The main objects of management accounting are expenses, costs, costs and revenues of the enterprise,

09:37.200 --> 09:46.200
as well as the results of the enterprise's work as a comparison of the enterprise's income and expenses.

09:46.200 --> 09:57.200
Such accounting objects as the centers of responsibility and the internal accounting system are always allocated.

09:59.200 --> 10:04.200
The methods used in management accounting are very diverse,

10:04.200 --> 10:09.200
as it combines the methods of many disciplines.

10:09.200 --> 10:17.200
This includes both operational accounting, accounting accounting, statistical accounting,

10:17.200 --> 10:30.200
analysis of strategic and operational planning, management of the enterprise's economy, statistics, mathematics.

10:31.200 --> 10:36.200
The growth of the scale of business, changes in technology,

10:36.200 --> 10:43.200
as well as the increase in the educational level of managers over the past decade

10:43.200 --> 10:47.200
have activated the development of management accounting

10:47.200 --> 10:55.200
and led to its wide recognition as a separate area of accounting, different from financial accounting.

10:55.200 --> 11:05.200
The goal of management accounting is to help managers make effective management decisions.

11:05.200 --> 11:09.200
It is realized in its tasks.

11:09.200 --> 11:19.200
This is the formation of reliable and complete information about the internal economic processes and the results of the activity.

11:19.200 --> 11:24.200
The presentation of this information is given by the enterprise's management

11:24.200 --> 11:29.200
by the internal management accounting.

11:29.200 --> 11:39.200
This is planning and control of the enterprise's economic efficiency and its centers of responsibility.

11:39.200 --> 11:45.200
This is the calculation of the actual cost of the product, work and services,

11:45.200 --> 11:51.200
the determination of deviations from management standards, standards, standards,

11:51.200 --> 11:55.200
the analysis of deviations from the planned results,

11:55.200 --> 11:59.200
the determination of the causes of these deviations,

11:59.200 --> 12:07.200
the control over the presence and movement of the property of material, financial, labor resources.

12:07.200 --> 12:12.200
This is the formation of an information base for decision-making.

12:12.200 --> 12:20.200
This is the realization of the reserves of increasing the efficiency of the enterprise's activities.

12:20.200 --> 12:28.200
Management influences are realized by means of the main functions of management,

12:28.200 --> 12:38.200
the interconnection and interaction of which form a closed, repeating, cyclical circle of management.

12:39.200 --> 12:48.200
This is planning, organization, accounting, control, regulation, analysis,

12:48.200 --> 12:53.200
and again planning, organization, accounting, and so on.

12:53.200 --> 13:03.200
Government accounting is a system of accounting, planning, control, analysis of income and expenses

13:03.200 --> 13:06.200
and the results of the organization's activities,

13:06.200 --> 13:15.200
in the necessary analytical sections of the operational acceptance of various management decisions.

13:15.200 --> 13:21.200
A specialist in management accounting for the execution of its functions

13:21.200 --> 13:28.200
must possess all the information, including confidential information.

13:28.200 --> 13:37.200
It must have the right to prepare its own special opinion with analytical, justified statements.

13:37.200 --> 13:44.200
It must have the right to postpone the decision-making in order to professionally prepare it.

13:44.200 --> 13:52.200
Tax accounting is carried out in strict accordance with the Tax Code.

13:53.200 --> 14:00.200
Tax accounting is a system of information generalization for determining the tax base

14:00.200 --> 14:04.200
on the basis of the data of primary documents,

14:04.200 --> 14:10.200
grouped in accordance with the order provided by the Tax Code.

14:10.200 --> 14:17.200
Tax accounting is carried out in order to form complete and reliable information

14:17.200 --> 14:23.200
on the order of accounting for the purpose of taxing economic operations

14:23.200 --> 14:28.200
carried out by taxpayers during the accounting period,

14:28.200 --> 14:34.200
as well as to provide information to internal and external users

14:34.200 --> 14:38.200
for the control of the correctness of the calculation,

14:38.200 --> 14:44.200
completeness and timeliness of the calculation, and payment of taxes to the budget.

14:44.200 --> 14:54.200
Tax accounting does not perform the functions of collecting and registering information on the facts of economic activity.

14:54.200 --> 15:00.200
These operations remain in the accounting knowledge.

15:00.200 --> 15:07.200
Subsequent processing of the collected information in order to calculate the tax base

15:07.200 --> 15:10.200
constitutes the subject of tax accounting.

15:10.200 --> 15:17.200
Tax accounting is based on the system of primary accounting

15:17.200 --> 15:25.200
and on the way of registering the facts of economic activity provided by accounting.

15:25.200 --> 15:30.200
But it can also introduce its own primary documents,

15:30.200 --> 15:34.200
such as invoices.

15:34.200 --> 15:40.200
Tax accounting involves the application of tax registers,

15:40.200 --> 15:45.200
in which information is generalized.

15:45.200 --> 15:49.200
In order to calculate, for example, the added cost of taxes,

15:49.200 --> 15:56.200
two special registers are formed â€“ the purchase book and the sale book.

15:56.200 --> 16:01.200
The forms of these registers are set up by law.

16:01.200 --> 16:04.200
In order to calculate the tax revenue,

16:04.200 --> 16:12.200
the organization develops the system of tax registers and their composition on its own,

16:12.200 --> 16:19.200
based on the principle of consistency of the application of the norms and rules of tax accounting.

16:19.200 --> 16:23.200
That is, the system of registers is applied in a sequence,

16:23.200 --> 16:28.200
from one tax period to another tax period.

16:28.200 --> 16:34.200
The order of tax accounting is established by the tax payer

16:34.200 --> 16:39.200
in the accounting policy for the purposes of tax deductions.

16:39.200 --> 16:46.200
Financial accounting is designed for the characteristics of the financial situation

16:46.200 --> 16:49.200
and the results of financial activity.

16:49.200 --> 16:55.200
The definition of the economic effectiveness of the enterprise's activities

16:55.200 --> 17:02.200
In financial accounting, information is formed about the income and expenses of the organization,

17:02.200 --> 17:08.200
about the libidin and credit debt, about financial investments,

17:08.200 --> 17:12.200
about the state of the financing sources,

17:12.200 --> 17:16.200
about the relationship with the state on the payment of taxes.

17:16.200 --> 17:23.200
The goal of financial accounting is to provide information about the financial situation,

17:23.200 --> 17:29.200
the results of activities and about the changes in the financial situation of the company.

17:29.200 --> 17:38.200
The financial situation of the company gives us a balance of this company.

17:40.200 --> 17:46.200
Information about the results of activities gives us a report on profits and losses.

17:46.200 --> 17:53.200
The financial situation of the company gives us separate reports.

17:53.200 --> 18:00.200
A report on capital changes, a report on the movement of money.

18:00.200 --> 18:07.200
Financial accounting shows the results of the company's management activities,

18:08.200 --> 18:19.200
as well as all the necessary information for decision-making.

18:21.200 --> 18:28.200
To make economic decisions, it is necessary to assess the ability of the enterprise

18:28.200 --> 18:35.200
to generate cash flows, deadlines and the definition of their generation,

18:35.200 --> 18:39.200
information about the results of profitability,

18:39.200 --> 18:45.200
we need to assess the potential changes in the controlled resources,

18:45.200 --> 18:48.200
the forecast of the generated cash flows,

18:48.200 --> 18:52.200
the effectiveness of the use of additional resources.

18:52.200 --> 18:59.200
Consumers, mainly external to the enterprise,

19:00.200 --> 19:05.200
are the tax authorities, banks, exchanges, other financial institutions,

19:05.200 --> 19:13.200
as well as suppliers, buyers, potential and real investors, employees of the enterprise.

19:13.200 --> 19:23.200
Financial accounting must be assured by an independent auditor or audit firm.

19:24.200 --> 19:28.200
Financial accounting is public.

19:28.200 --> 19:32.200
It is intended for publication.

19:32.200 --> 19:45.200
The publicity of individual accounting becomes a kind of advertising of the company's activities.

19:46.200 --> 19:49.200
Companies make colorful booklets,

19:49.200 --> 19:53.200
where they provide their reports,

19:53.200 --> 19:58.200
provide information about the company's activities,

19:58.200 --> 20:02.200
post open information on the Internet,

20:02.200 --> 20:06.200
publish it in special publications.

20:16.200 --> 20:20.200
Financial accounting

20:26.200 --> 20:36.200
All financial information is made up of standards.

20:37.200 --> 20:46.200
Standards can be national or international.

20:50.200 --> 20:56.200
The goal of the standards is to provide users with reliable,

20:56.200 --> 21:00.200
accessible information about the financial situation

21:00.200 --> 21:04.200
and the results of the company's financial activities

21:04.200 --> 21:08.200
that are useful for making economic decisions.

21:10.200 --> 21:16.200
We often come across the English abbreviation GAAP,

21:16.200 --> 21:21.200
especially when it is written as USA.

21:22.200 --> 21:31.200
We think that it refers only to the standards in the United States.

21:31.200 --> 21:40.200
No, GAAP is translated from English as the General Principles of Accounting.

21:40.200 --> 21:45.200
GAAP is a system of rules, requirements,

21:45.200 --> 21:49.200
and practices of financial accounting

21:49.200 --> 21:54.200
that are adopted and applied in a certain jurisdiction.

21:54.200 --> 22:00.200
The designation of a state before the abbreviation

22:00.200 --> 22:04.200
defines this jurisdiction.

22:07.200 --> 22:11.200
The composition and representation of financial accounting

22:11.200 --> 22:18.200
by any country is regulated by a set of standards.

22:18.200 --> 22:23.200
The system of national accounting standards

22:23.200 --> 22:28.200
is developed by special organizations,

22:28.200 --> 22:32.200
based on theoretical research,

22:32.200 --> 22:39.200
and is mandatory for the country's level of performance.

22:39.200 --> 22:44.200
The system of national accounting standards

22:44.200 --> 22:49.200
is regulated by the government's laws,

22:49.200 --> 22:54.200
regulations, and directives.

22:54.200 --> 22:59.200
It defines the methods of accounting

22:59.200 --> 23:04.200
and the evaluation of the production of stocks and other material values.

23:04.200 --> 23:09.200
It regulates the amortization of foreign assets,

23:09.200 --> 23:14.200
regulates accounting forms and indicators,

23:14.200 --> 23:19.200
defines external methods of controlling the company's activities,

23:19.200 --> 23:24.200
contains the national accounting plan,

23:24.200 --> 23:29.200
and provides the user with sufficient information

23:29.200 --> 23:34.200
to make decisions at the micro and macro levels.

23:34.200 --> 23:38.200
The national standards can be

23:38.200 --> 23:41.200
the GAAP of the USA, the GAAP of the UK,

23:41.200 --> 23:44.200
the GAAP of Germany, the GAAP of France,

23:44.200 --> 23:49.200
the GAAP of Russia, the GAAP of any country.

23:49.200 --> 23:53.200
In addition to national standards,

23:53.200 --> 23:57.200
regional standards are developed,

23:57.200 --> 24:01.200
which are mandatory for all members

24:01.200 --> 24:05.200
of the region.

24:05.200 --> 24:08.200
For example, the EU directives

24:08.200 --> 24:12.200
and other regional standards.

24:14.200 --> 24:20.200
If we look at the national standards of certain countries,

24:21.200 --> 24:26.200
we will notice that all countries

24:26.200 --> 24:31.200
can approach the reflection of certain assets,

24:31.200 --> 24:34.200
obligations in different ways.

24:34.200 --> 24:38.200
For example, in Denmark, Spain, Russia, France,

24:38.200 --> 24:41.200
and in a number of other countries,

24:41.200 --> 24:44.200
the main funds are taken into account

24:44.200 --> 24:47.200
according to the initial cost.

24:47.200 --> 24:50.200
In the UK, the main funds are taken into account

24:50.200 --> 24:53.200
according to the initial cost or the market cost.

24:53.200 --> 24:56.200
In Belgium, the main funds are taken into account

24:56.200 --> 25:02.200
according to the initial cost or the market cost.

25:02.200 --> 25:05.200
The revaluation of the main funds, for example,

25:05.200 --> 25:12.200
is not applied in the USA, Luxembourg, Japan,

25:12.200 --> 25:14.200
and a number of other countries,

25:14.200 --> 25:17.200
but is either done in a series of steps

25:17.200 --> 25:23.200
by the government bodies in Greece, Spain, and Italy,

25:23.200 --> 25:26.200
or is a permanent practice,

25:26.200 --> 25:29.200
as in the UK, Germany, the Netherlands,

25:29.200 --> 25:32.200
Russia, France, and Sweden.

25:32.200 --> 25:36.200
The revaluation can cover various periods.

25:36.200 --> 25:41.200
For example, in the UK, real estate is revalued

25:41.200 --> 25:44.200
no less than once every five years.

25:44.200 --> 25:47.200
In Denmark, every six months,

25:47.200 --> 25:50.200
the conditions and terms of amortization

25:50.200 --> 25:54.200
of non-returnable assets are changed.

25:54.200 --> 25:57.200
That is, the main funds, non-material assets.

25:57.200 --> 26:00.200
For example, the term of amortization

26:00.200 --> 26:04.200
of the business reputation in Belgium is five years.

26:04.200 --> 26:07.200
In the Netherlands, it is ten years.

26:08.200 --> 26:12.200
In Russia and France, it is twenty years.

26:12.200 --> 26:17.200
In the UK, the full calculation of its value

26:17.200 --> 26:21.200
and the funds of the previously listed reserves

26:21.200 --> 26:24.200
is carried out immediately.

26:24.200 --> 26:28.200
As a result, the incompatibility of indicators

26:28.200 --> 26:31.200
of various national systems.

26:32.200 --> 26:38.200
Thus, the income for the share of one Russian enterprise

26:38.200 --> 26:42.200
calculated according to the national accounting standards

26:42.200 --> 26:45.200
of the UK, Germany, and France

26:45.200 --> 26:50.200
was 6, 3, and 4 dollars.

26:50.200 --> 26:53.200
Three systems are highlighted.

26:53.200 --> 26:58.200
This is the Anglo-American financial accounting model.

26:59.200 --> 27:02.200
This is the continental model.

27:02.200 --> 27:05.200
And this is the Latin American model.

27:05.200 --> 27:10.200
The Anglo-American model combines the accounting systems

27:10.200 --> 27:17.200
of the countries that used to be part of the British Commonwealth.

27:17.200 --> 27:21.200
These are Australia, Great Britain, Hong Kong, Israel,

27:21.200 --> 27:26.200
India, Canada, Cyprus, Netherlands, USA, and some other countries.

27:29.200 --> 27:34.200
The continental model combines the national accounting systems

27:34.200 --> 27:39.200
of such countries as Germany, Austria, Belgium, Greece,

27:39.200 --> 27:44.200
Denmark, Spain, France, Switzerland, and Sweden.

27:44.200 --> 27:48.200
The national accounting system in Russia and Japan

27:48.200 --> 27:52.200
is close to this model.

27:52.200 --> 27:58.200
The Latin American model combines the national accounting systems

27:58.200 --> 28:03.200
of the countries of South America in terms of language

28:03.200 --> 28:06.200
and in terms of the common past.

28:08.200 --> 28:13.200
In all the countries that are part of the Anglo-American model,

28:13.200 --> 28:18.200
the USA and Great Britain have a great influence.

28:19.200 --> 28:22.200
The accounting practices of the countries

28:22.200 --> 28:25.200
that are part of the continental model

28:25.200 --> 28:28.200
are significantly different from each other.

28:28.200 --> 28:33.200
A distinctive feature of the accounting system of the countries

28:33.200 --> 28:38.200
that are part of the Latin American model

28:38.200 --> 28:42.200
is the adjustment to inflation.

28:42.200 --> 28:47.200
The Anglo-American model assumes

28:47.200 --> 28:54.200
that the market for securities is well developed in these countries.

28:54.200 --> 28:59.200
This is why there is a high level of professionalism

28:59.200 --> 29:04.200
in the accounting system of both accountants and users.

29:04.200 --> 29:08.200
The accounting system is primarily aimed

29:09.200 --> 29:13.200
at the needs of investors and creditors.

29:13.200 --> 29:18.200
In the countries that use the continental model,

29:18.200 --> 29:22.200
business has a close relationship with banks.

29:22.200 --> 29:26.200
The orientation of financial accounting

29:26.200 --> 29:32.200
to the needs of investors is not a priority here.

29:32.200 --> 29:39.200
In the countries that use the Latin American model,

29:39.200 --> 29:43.200
accounting is generally oriented to the needs

29:43.200 --> 29:46.200
of state and tax authorities.

29:46.200 --> 29:50.200
There is strict control in these countries

29:50.200 --> 29:53.200
over the implementation of tax policy.

29:53.200 --> 29:57.200
The Anglo-American model is particularly important

29:57.200 --> 30:01.200
in calculating the real financial result.

30:01.200 --> 30:06.200
The task of providing information to the state

30:06.200 --> 30:09.200
in the face of tax authorities

30:09.200 --> 30:13.200
is generally carried out within the framework of financial accounting

30:13.200 --> 30:16.200
and financial reporting.

30:16.200 --> 30:20.200
In the continental accounting model,

30:20.200 --> 30:24.200
accounting is regulated by law,

30:24.200 --> 30:28.200
differs in a large degree from conservatism,

30:28.200 --> 30:33.200
and the state's interference in accounting

30:33.200 --> 30:38.200
is usually a requirement for the use of accounts.

30:38.200 --> 30:43.200
Accounting is oriented to the satisfaction

30:43.200 --> 30:52.200
of information needs of tax and other state authorities.

