35:23.200 --> 35:28.200
The main reason is that the International Standards Committee,

35:28.200 --> 35:34.200
even in its formation of accounting in compliance with the International Standards Committee,

35:34.200 --> 35:39.200
allows companies to join the capital market.

35:39.200 --> 35:43.200
Capital in the face of investors requires

35:43.200 --> 35:47.200
the company to be open, transparent,

35:47.200 --> 35:52.200
and accountable to investors.

35:52.200 --> 35:56.200
If an investor is deprived of the opportunity

35:56.200 --> 35:59.200
to monitor the use of capital invested in a company

35:59.200 --> 36:03.200
with the help of financial accountability,

36:03.200 --> 36:06.200
such a company will always remain

36:06.200 --> 36:10.200
an area of increased risk for the investor

36:10.200 --> 36:14.200
and, accordingly, will always lose

36:14.200 --> 36:17.200
compared to other companies

36:17.200 --> 36:22.200
in attracting financial resources from the capital market.

36:22.200 --> 36:27.200
If a company does not have the accountability required,

36:27.200 --> 36:30.200
then from the investor's point of view

36:30.200 --> 36:33.200
it does not deserve trust

36:33.200 --> 36:36.200
and cannot be competitively capable

36:36.200 --> 36:40.200
on par with other capital seekers.

36:40.200 --> 36:44.200
Financial accountability formed in compliance with the International Standards Committee

36:44.200 --> 36:50.200
is distinguished by high informativeness and usefulness for the user.

36:50.200 --> 36:53.200
The use of the International Standards Committee

36:53.200 --> 36:57.200
allows to significantly reduce the time and resources

36:57.200 --> 37:00.200
required to develop national standards.

37:00.200 --> 37:03.200
