What is continuity of activity? It means that an organization, once created, continues its work indefinitely. It is clear that no living organism can exist indefinitely, so it is called permissibility.

01:00:43.200 --> 01:01:06.200
It is necessary to make an accounting financial accounting based on this permissibility. It is necessary to assess the ability of a company to continue its activity in the near future.

01:01:06.200 --> 01:01:17.200
It is also necessary to reveal the facts of significant uncertainty that may affect the continuity of the organization's activities.

01:01:36.200 --> 01:01:53.200
The concept of the convergence of received income and spent expenses is a recognition of assets, obligations, income and expenses at the time of their occurrence, not payment.

01:01:53.200 --> 01:02:09.200
One of the quality characteristics of financial accounting is its clarity.

01:02:09.200 --> 01:02:30.200
It does not mean that clarity should be clear to the first-time user. It is assumed that a financial accounting user should have sufficient knowledge in the field of business and commercial activity, a desire to study information with due diligence.

01:02:31.200 --> 01:02:58.200
It does not mean that the complicated information that should be included in financial accounting, due to its compatibility with the decision-making process, should be excluded, only because it may be too difficult for certain users to understand.

01:02:59.200 --> 01:03:07.200
The next quality characteristic of financial accounting is its compatibility.

01:03:07.200 --> 01:03:19.200
Different periods within a company should be comparable. The financial accountability of various companies should be comparable.

01:03:19.200 --> 01:03:36.200
A consistent approach to the assessment and reflection of the financial result should be provided. Information on accounting policies and changes in accounting policies should be presented.

01:03:36.200 --> 01:03:53.200
The compatibility of information is the balance between its temporality and reliability.

01:03:53.200 --> 01:04:05.200
The later the period of information, the more reliable the information is, that is, it is free of many errors.

01:04:23.200 --> 01:04:39.200
Therefore, the balance between temporality and reliability should be observed, because no one needs old, outdated information.

01:04:39.200 --> 01:04:56.200
Users want to receive information on time. The costs of providing information should not exceed the benefits of the information provided.

01:04:56.200 --> 01:05:25.200
The information should be presented only in significant sections. Information is considered significant if its absence or incorrect assessment may affect the decision of the user based on the data of the financial account.

01:05:26.200 --> 01:05:39.200
The significance depends on the size, the threshold or the point of the account. The information should be reliable, that is, free of significant errors.

01:05:39.200 --> 01:05:52.200
A reliable presentation of the account means compliance with all the criteria of recognition. This is a priority of the content before the form.

01:05:52.200 --> 01:06:10.200
We represent the economic essence of the event, not its legal form. The information should be neutral, that is, not in anyone's interests.

01:06:10.200 --> 01:06:28.200
The principle of review should be observed. In the event of uncertainty, the income and assets should not be increased, the expenses and obligations should not be reduced.

01:06:28.200 --> 01:06:51.200
The information should be presented in all its entirety, that is, in all significant sections, without any omissions. The connection between significance and costs of benefits should be ensured.

01:06:52.200 --> 01:07:04.200
A reliable presentation of the financial account is the correct application of international standards. This is a choice of relevant accounting policies.

01:07:04.200 --> 01:07:14.200
